## ComBus header architecture — IS_MACHINE guard pattern (2026-03-09)

### Problem solved
The project had two parallel umbrella files (combus.h + combus_types.h) and two
parallel leaf files (dumper_truck.h + dumper_truck_types.h). Adding a new machine
required updating four files. The split existed because machines_struct.h needed
the enum IDs (AnalogComBusID, DigitalComBusID) but could not include the full
dumper_truck.h without creating an include cycle.

### Root cause
machines_struct.h used std::optional<AnalogComBusID> as a field type.
The compiler only needs the *size* of the enum for that — not the enumerator values.
C++11 allows forward-declaring a scoped enum with its underlying type:

    enum class AnalogComBusID  : uint8_t;   // forward — no values, size is known
    enum class DigitalComBusID : uint8_t;

Placing these two lines in machines_struct.h (instead of #include <combus_types.h>)
breaks the cycle permanently and structurally — no umbrella trick needed.

### Resulting architecture

    combus.h  — sole umbrella, all consumers include this
      └─ dumper_truck.h
           ├── Section 1 (always): AnalogComBusID / DigitalComBusID enum definitions
           └── Section 2 (#ifdef IS_MACHINE only):
                 - #include <struct/combus_struct.h>
                 - extern AnalogComBusArray / DigitalComBusArray / comBus
                 - #include includes_map/inputs_map.h

IS_MACHINE is defined via -D IS_MACHINE in [env:machines] in platformio.ini.
It is absent for the sound node and remote node environments.
Do NOT remove or rename IS_MACHINE — the split between section 1 and section 2
of every machine combus file depends on it.

### Adding a new machine
1. Create src/core/config/combus/new_machine/new_machine.h following the two-section
   pattern of dumper_truck.h.
2. Add one #elif branch in combus.h.
That is all — no second file, no second umbrella.

### VSCode explorer note
After deleting files from the terminal (e.g. Remove-Item), VSCode's file explorer
may still show the deleted entries until manually refreshed.
Fix: right-click the parent folder in the Explorer panel -> Refresh, or
Ctrl+Shift+P -> File: Refresh Explorer.


